
ARM = *Advanced Risc Machines* (previously *Acorn Risc Machine*). In 2013, 60% of mobile devices contained ARM-based chips.
It now has a monopoly on handheld devices.

ARM is a family of RISC (Reduced Instruction Set Computer) architectures.

ARM Holdings Inc. is a *fabless* semiconductor company: they design chips and the license their technology to semiconductor producing companies such as ATMEL, NXP or Samsung.
